\c 36
\p
\v 1 For the director, of the servant of YHWH, of David
\q1
\v 2 Transgression speaks to the wicked in the midst of his heart,\f + Ps 15:2; 24:4?.\f*
\q1 There is no terror of God before his eyes.
\q1
\v 3 For he flatters himself in his eyes,
\q1 To find his guilt and to hate.\f + Meaning uncertain; compare translations.\f*
\q1
\v 4 The words of his mouth are trouble and deceit,\f + Ps 15:2, 24:4.\f*
\q1 He ceases to understand and to do good.
\q1
\v 5 Trouble he plans on his bed,
\q1 He sets himself on a way that is not good,
\q1 he does not reject evil.\f + Ps 15:3.\f*
\q1
\v 6 O YHWH, in the heavens is your steadfast love,
\q1 Your faithfulness to the clouds.
\q1
\v 7 Your righteousness is like the mountains of God,
\q1 Your judgments, the great deep,
\q1 Man and animal you save, O YHWH.
\q1
\v 8 How precious is your steadfast love, O GOd,
\q1 The children of man take refuge in the shadow of your wings.
\q1
\v 9 They drink their fill of the fat of your house\f + Ps 15:1; 24:3.\f*,
\q1 And from the river of your joy you give them drink.
\q1
\v 10 For with you is the fountain of life,
\q1 In your light we see light.
\q1
\v 11 Extend your steadfast love to those who know you,
\q1 And your righteousness to the upright of heart.\f + Ps 24:4.\f*
\q1
\v 12 Do not let the foot of haughtiness come to me,
\q1 And let not the hand of the wicked make me homeless.
\q1
\v 13 There evildoers fall,
\q1 They are overturned and they are not able to rise.\f + \ft Ps 15:5.\f*